    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-pim-bfd-p2mp-use-case-10.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-pim-bfd-p2mp-use-case-10.txt</link>
        <title>"Fast Failover in Protocol Independent Multicast - Sparse Mode (PIM-SM) Using Bidirectional Forwarding Detection (BFD) for Multipoint Networks", Greg Mirsky, Ji Xiaoli</title>
        <dc:date>2021-12-09T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This document specifies how Bidirectional Forwarding Detection for multipoint networks can provide sub-second failover for routers that participate in Protocol Independent Multicast - Sparse Mode (PIM-SM). An extension to the PIM Hello message used to bootstrap a point-to- multipoint BFD session is also defined in this document.</description>
    </item>
